18#include "QRDataBlock.h"
19#include "QRVersion.h"
20#include "QRErrorCorrectionLevel.h"
21#include "DecodeStatus.h"

24namespace ZXing {
25namespace QRCode {
26
27std::vector<DataBlock> DataBlock::GetDataBlocks(const ByteArray& rawCodewords, const Version& version, ErrorCorrectionLevel ecLevel)
28{
29 if (Size(rawCodewords) != version.totalCodewords())
30 return {};
31
32 // Figure out the number and size of data blocks used by this version and
33 // error correction level
34 auto& ecBlocks = version.ecBlocksForLevel(ecLevel);
35
36 // First count the total number of data blocks
37 int totalBlocks = ecBlocks.numBlocks();
38
39 std::vector<DataBlock> result(totalBlocks);
40 // Now establish DataBlocks of the appropriate size and number of data codewords
41 int numResultBlocks = 0;
42 for (auto& ecBlock : ecBlocks.blockArray()) {
43 for (int i = 0; i < ecBlock.count; i++) {
44 auto& item = result[numResultBlocks++];
45 item._numDataCodewords = ecBlock.dataCodewords;
46 item._codewords.resize(ecBlocks.codewordsPerBlock + ecBlock.dataCodewords);
47 }
48 }
49
50 // All blocks have the same amount of data, except that the last n
51 // (where n may be 0) have 1 more byte. Figure out where these start.
52 int shorterBlocksTotalCodewords = Size(result[0]._codewords);
53 int longerBlocksStartAt = Size(result) - 1;
54 while (longerBlocksStartAt >= 0) {
55 int numCodewords = Size(result[longerBlocksStartAt]._codewords);
56 if (numCodewords == shorterBlocksTotalCodewords) {
57 break;
58 }
59 longerBlocksStartAt--;
60 }
61 longerBlocksStartAt++;
62
63 int shorterBlocksNumDataCodewords = shorterBlocksTotalCodewords - ecBlocks.codewordsPerBlock;
64 // The last elements of result may be 1 element longer;
65 // first fill out as many elements as all of them have
66 int rawCodewordsOffset = 0;
67 for (int i = 0; i < shorterBlocksNumDataCodewords; i++) {
68 for (int j = 0; j < numResultBlocks; j++) {
69 result[j]._codewords[i] = rawCodewords[rawCodewordsOffset++];
70 }
71 }
72 // Fill out the last data block in the longer ones
73 for (int j = longerBlocksStartAt; j < numResultBlocks; j++) {
74 result[j]._codewords[shorterBlocksNumDataCodewords] = rawCodewords[rawCodewordsOffset++];
75 }
76 // Now add in error correction blocks
77 int max = Size(result[0]._codewords);
78 for (int i = shorterBlocksNumDataCodewords; i < max; i++) {
79 for (int j = 0; j < numResultBlocks; j++) {
80 int iOffset = j < longerBlocksStartAt ? i : i + 1;
81 result[j]._codewords[iOffset] = rawCodewords[rawCodewordsOffset++];
82 }
83 }
84 return result;
85}
